FW ORION DASHMessage From Ryan Bekerman Joana Sent Wednesday June PM To McCoppin Dorothy Shankman Jeffrey A Subject FW ORION DASH This one of the transactions that Per David mentioned to you last week Note that this is a draft but we wanted to give you a chance to review this as it will be coming through in the next two days for execution Regards Joana Original Message From Ryan Bekerman Joana Sent Wednesday June AM To Schneider Chip Nordstrom Mary Hagelmann Bjorn Cc Hoog David Sekse Per Subject ORION DASH All Attached please find the draft ORION DASH The counterparty is anxious to execute this week we are in final contract negotiations Please review and contact us with any questions Note that this is slightly different as it is primarily a physical deal and the deductibles are calculated based on a weather index regards Joana Joana Ryan Bekerman Enron Global Markets Tel Fax

PeakersForwarded by Joana Ryan BekermanNAEnron on PM Joana Ryan Bekerman AM To cc Subject Peakers Ben Attached is the latest draft of the Beck report Im attaching a list that I prepared that generally has the items that are outstanding however the priority items are the back up information on performance testing curves of the inlet fogging system and the peaking testing output of the three units and the confirmation of the data in table long term performance of the projects I have the OM contracts the monthly reports and the contracts between OEC and Caldwell for the inlet fogging system but these do not contain what Conrad RW Beck is looking for My understanding from the operations guys is that there is data for the above items As discussed Conrad will be here Monday morning so if we could have the back up information for these items by then it would expedite the process tremendously You can reach me at if you have any questions Thanks for your help Joana
